My name is Tae Yamakura.

249
00:16:12,610 --> 00:16:14,700
Come on, introduce yourself, too.

250
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:15,880
(Suzu Chika, 19, Geisha)
Okay.

251
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:19,920
(Suzu Chika, 19, Geisha)
My name is Suzu Chika, nice to meet you.

252
00:16:23,410 --> 00:16:25,410
How can I thank you?

253
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:28,010
No need, it's not a big deal.

254
00:16:28,210 --> 00:16:31,110
Come hang out at the store next time.

255
00:16:32,410 --> 00:16:33,610
Be safe on the way back.

256
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:35,010
Thanks.

257
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:49,410
What does this painting mean?

258
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:52,710
On the fifth row on top,

259
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:55,410
there's a cicada, a tengu, and a goldfish.

260
00:16:55,910 --> 00:17:00,810
On the fourth row, there's a chicken and a loach.

261
00:17:01,210 --> 00:17:04,010
The yellow loach is really disgusting.

262
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:06,510
What is this dot?

263
00:17:06,710 --> 00:17:07,810
Is it dirt?

264
00:17:08,810 --> 00:17:10,910
In the middle of the second and third row,

265
00:17:11,410 --> 00:17:13,610
there's a violet, tengu, and Mount Fuji.

266
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:16,010
There's also an acorn next to it.

267
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:20,810
Dad, can you find it before the day after tomorrow?

268
00:17:21,210 --> 00:17:22,710
Don't worry.

269
00:17:23,110 --> 00:17:26,510
This kind of painting doesn't even constitute a riddle for me.

270
00:17:26,710 --> 00:17:28,810
Hey, seriously?

271
00:17:30,010 --> 00:17:32,110
I'll leave it to the experts to find the Buddha statue.

272
00:17:32,310 --> 00:17:34,610
Let's go and visit Kyoto.

273
00:17:35,210 --> 00:17:36,410
That's it.

274
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,810
You will only disturb me here.

275
00:17:39,210 --> 00:17:42,210
Actually, I've already gotten in touch with Toyama,

276
00:17:42,210 --> 00:17:44,710
and I asked her to be our Kyoto tour guide tomorrow.

277
00:17:45,210 --> 00:17:48,410
But Hattori seems to have something going on and he can't come.

278
00:17:48,710 --> 00:17:51,610
It doesn't matter if the boys
who already have girlfriends come or not.

279
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:54,610
That guy is not coming?

280
00:17:55,610 --> 00:17:57,410
Conan, let's go together.

281
00:17:58,010 --> 00:17:59,410
I won't be going.

282
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:03,010
I have a date with a kid nearby to go fishing by the river.

283
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:05,610
You've made friends so soon.

284
00:18:06,010 --> 00:18:07,110
Be careful.

285
00:18:09,810 --> 00:18:11,810
First of all, it seems that the Buddha statue
was stolen from Sannou Temple.

286
00:18:12,410 --> 00:18:14,110
It must be Genjibotaru.

287
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:19,110
But who on earth sent this painting, and for what purpose?

288
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:22,710
And what does it have to do with the five murder cases?

289
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:26,310
Genjibotaru...

290
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:29,110
Talking about Yoshitsune and Benkei,

291
00:18:29,610 --> 00:18:31,210
it should still be there.

292
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:41,250
(Gojou Bridge)

293
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:49,110
Nothing seems to be related to the riddle in the painting.

294
00:18:50,710 --> 00:18:53,310
On the Gojou Bridge in Kyoto,

295
00:18:53,710 --> 00:18:58,210
the strongman Benkei wields a long sword

296
00:18:58,210 --> 00:19:00,410
and initiates an attack toward Ushiwakamaru.

297
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:06,210
Hattori…

298
00:19:07,210 --> 00:19:11,110
I can't believe that I'd meet you here.

299
00:19:12,410 --> 00:19:15,010
Hey, give me the bamboo knife.

300
00:19:16,610 --> 00:19:18,210
Sorry. Thank you.

301
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:19,510
Hey, let's go.

302
00:19:23,110 --> 00:19:24,610
Work hard on your practice.

303
00:19:25,510 --> 00:19:27,110
Why did you borrow a bamboo knife?

304
00:19:27,910 --> 00:19:30,510
What are you doing in this kind of place?

305
00:19:31,210 --> 00:19:32,910
And what are you doing here?

306
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:39,410
Actually I know the owner of the Takoyaki shop
who was killed in Osaka.

307
00:19:40,610 --> 00:19:43,210
Although he was a member of a robber's gang,

308
00:19:43,810 --> 00:19:46,210
I used to go to that store since I was in junior high school

309
00:19:46,910 --> 00:19:48,210
and he took good care of me, so

310
00:19:48,710 --> 00:19:51,310
I wanted to find the murderer for him.

311
00:19:51,810 --> 00:19:56,410
That's why you came to Kyoto looking for clues.

312
00:19:56,810 --> 00:19:58,710
In this case, I have something to show you.

313
00:20:04,210 --> 00:20:05,310
I see.

314
00:20:06,110 --> 00:20:08,010
If you solve the riddle in this painting,

315
00:20:08,010 --> 00:20:09,610
you might not only find the Buddha statue,

316
00:20:09,610 --> 00:20:12,110
but also the murderer.

317
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:14,210
So you...

318
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:17,810
Yes, if it is Genjibotaru who stole the Buddha statue,

319
00:20:18,410 --> 00:20:20,810
then we might find clues to solving the riddle

320
00:20:21,010 --> 00:20:24,510
in places related to Yoshitsune and Benkei.

321
00:20:25,410 --> 00:20:27,210
But I am not familiar with Kyoto at all.

322
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:29,410
Then leave it to me.

323
00:20:30,010 --> 00:20:31,310
I will show you the way.

324
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,310
(Gojyoten Shrine)

325
00:20:37,310 --> 00:20:38,960
(Gojyoten Shrine)
This is Gojyoten Shrine.

326
00:20:39,810 --> 00:20:42,410
"Chronicles of Yoshitsune" records
that the two weren't on the Gojyouoohashi bridge,

327
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:44,810
instead, they met here for the first time.

328
00:20:46,110 --> 00:20:49,210
How is it? Is there anything in common?

329
00:20:51,510 --> 00:20:52,710
Doesn't look like it.

330
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:54,510
Then let's head to the next place,

331
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:56,710
That's really upsetting.

332
00:20:58,110 --> 00:21:01,910
Why didn't the monks at Sannou Temple come to me?

333
00:21:02,310 --> 00:21:04,810
When it comes to detectives in Kansai, it should be me, right?

334
00:21:05,110 --> 00:21:09,110
Maybe they didn't want the police to know,

335
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:12,610
since your dad is a senior police officer.

336
00:21:14,510 --> 00:21:15,710
Forget it.

337
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:19,810
Wait, in that case…

338
00:21:24,410 --> 00:21:25,610
Here it is. Right here.

339
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:31,140
(Benkei Stone)
Benkei Stone.

340
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:34,810
Some says that's the stone that Benkai often sat on,

341
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:36,810
while others say it is a stone thrown down from Mount Hie.

342
00:21:37,110 --> 00:21:39,110
In short, there are many legends.

343
00:21:39,710 --> 00:21:42,110
That doesn't seem to have anything to do with this either.

344
00:21:42,610 --> 00:21:43,310
Really?

345
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:44,910
Let's check out the next one then.

346
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:46,310
Where's the next one?

347
00:21:46,910 --> 00:21:48,610
Keage Slope.

348
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:53,110
I'm a Kyoto Prefecture police officer, Ayanokoji.

349
00:21:53,410 --> 00:21:57,110
I know you are investigating Genjibotaru's case,

350
00:21:57,410 --> 00:21:59,310
but this is not Osaka.

351
00:21:59,810 --> 00:22:01,310
It's best for the laymen not to be nosy.

352
00:22:09,310 --> 00:22:10,610
It's a chipmunk.

353
00:22:11,710 --> 00:22:12,710
Watch out for yourself.

354
00:22:17,610 --> 00:22:20,010
There are strange police officers like this everywhere.

355
00:22:20,970 --> 00:22:23,250
(Kiyomizudera Temple)

356
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:24,810
Let's take some pictures.

357
00:22:25,110 --> 00:22:26,910
Make sure you get the cherry blossoms, too.

358
00:22:26,910 --> 00:22:28,110
So beautiful.

359
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:31,510
If I get to see such a beautiful view with Kyogoku,

360
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:35,710
it'll be such a blessing.

361
00:22:35,810 --> 00:22:37,710
Ran, seriously.

362
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:40,010
It's my turn this time.

363
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:50,310
Toyama, did you have a fight with Hattori?

364
00:22:51,810 --> 00:22:55,710
Actually Heiji also came to Kyoto to investigate a case,

365
00:22:56,410 --> 00:22:59,910
and Heiji's first love is also in Kyoto.

366
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:07,570
(Keage Slope Canal Park)

367
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,890
(Perfected Great Sun Buddha)

368
00:23:13,110 --> 00:23:14,710
This doesn't seem to be right either.

369
00:23:16,210 --> 00:23:17,410
Let's go and grab lunch.

370
00:23:17,710 --> 00:23:18,210
OK.

371
00:23:27,810 --> 00:23:28,910
Cherry blossoms.

372
00:23:31,710 --> 00:23:34,210
I always recall what happened 8 years ago

373
00:23:34,610 --> 00:23:36,010
when I see cherry blossoms.

374
00:23:37,010 --> 00:23:39,210
At that time, I went on an adventure in temples in Kyoto,

375
00:23:39,910 --> 00:23:42,210
and I accidentally hit the lattice window of the temple.

376
00:23:43,310 --> 00:23:45,310
Even the wooden frame was broken.

377
00:23:46,310 --> 00:23:48,610
I hit my head hard on the floor

378
00:23:48,810 --> 00:23:50,310
and passed out.

379
00:23:51,910 --> 00:23:54,510
I was out for an unknown period of time.

380
00:23:54,810 --> 00:23:56,710
When I woke up…

381
00:23:56,810 --> 00:24:00,810
After Shichijo comes Hachi-Kujo

382
00:24:01,210 --> 00:24:05,910
Kujo, toji comes at the end.

383
00:24:06,510 --> 00:24:11,310
Maru-Take-Ebisu-Ni-Oshi-Oike

384
00:24:11,710 --> 00:24:16,410
Ane-San-Rokkaku-Tako-Nishiki

385
00:24:17,410 --> 00:24:22,210
Shi-Aya-Butsu-Taka-Matsu-Man-Gojo

386
00:24:22,610 --> 00:24:26,910
Setta-Chara, chara-Uonotana.

387
00:24:56,110 --> 00:24:57,010
It felt like a dream.

388
00:24:57,010 --> 00:24:58,610
But it was real.

389
00:25:01,610 --> 00:25:04,310
I always think we'll meet again.

390
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:10,310
What are you laughing about?

391
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:13,510
Sorry, please continue.

392
00:25:13,810 --> 00:25:16,810
I always bring this with me when I come to Kyoto.

393
00:25:18,610 --> 00:25:20,010
Crystal bead.

394
00:25:21,110 --> 00:25:22,910
I seem to have seen it somewhere.

395
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:24,010
Really?

396
00:25:24,610 --> 00:25:26,210
There's someone with the same crystal?

397
00:25:27,310 --> 00:25:28,010
No.

398
00:25:28,910 --> 00:25:31,810
So does she know about it?

399
00:25:32,110 --> 00:25:33,110
She?

400
00:25:33,610 --> 00:25:35,510
You mean Toyama?

401
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:38,010
Although I never told her the details,

402
00:25:38,010 --> 00:25:39,310
she seems to know.

403
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:42,410
She knew it because...

404
00:25:43,810 --> 00:25:45,510
The interview in the magazine.

405
00:25:45,810 --> 00:25:49,810
Yes, it is the most popular magazine in Kansai.

406
00:25:50,210 --> 00:25:53,410
Heiji was asked who his first love was,

407
00:25:54,010 --> 00:25:55,810
and he said she's someone he met in third grade of elementary school

408
00:25:55,810 --> 00:25:58,610
who's slightly older than him.

409
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:03,210
He also said he got a precious token from the girl,

410
00:26:03,510 --> 00:26:06,210
and went out of his way to pose for this photo.

411
00:26:07,010 --> 00:26:08,210
What is this?

412
00:26:08,710 --> 00:26:10,210
Just a crystal bead.

413
00:26:10,510 --> 00:26:12,410
Maybe that girl dropped it.

414
00:26:12,710 --> 00:26:15,210
So you know that girl?

415
00:26:15,210 --> 00:26:16,610
How would I?

416
00:26:17,610 --> 00:26:20,210
Heiji only met her once,

417
00:26:20,510 --> 00:26:23,110
so every time I come to Kyoto, I will ask about her.

418
00:26:24,310 --> 00:26:26,310
That's why he took the photos with the crystal bead.

419
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:28,610
He probably wanted that girl

420
00:26:28,610 --> 00:26:32,610
to get in touch with him after reading the interview.

421
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:34,810
Right, what a damn thing.

422
00:26:36,210 --> 00:26:39,310
He even posted a photo of himself as a kid.

423
00:26:40,910 --> 00:26:41,910
So cute.

424
00:26:42,110 --> 00:26:45,110
Right? Right? Heiji was super cute back then...

425
00:26:46,310 --> 00:26:49,410
Ran, this is not the point,

426
00:26:49,810 --> 00:26:51,910
but forget about it.

427
00:26:52,310 --> 00:26:55,010
Even if Hattori has a first love,

428
00:26:55,310 --> 00:26:56,910
that's already a thing of the past.

429
00:26:57,410 --> 00:27:00,210
And you two look like you're in a stable relationship.

430
00:27:00,610 --> 00:27:05,410
But first love is very special for men.

431
00:27:06,310 --> 00:27:07,510
Sonoko.

432
00:27:08,610 --> 00:27:11,410
Forget about it. Let's not talk about something so depressing.

433
00:27:11,810 --> 00:27:13,210
By the way, have some red bean soup.

434
00:27:13,910 --> 00:27:17,710
Boss, we want three bowls of red bean soup. Be quick please.

435
00:27:30,510 --> 00:27:32,810
There is the west gate of Kurama Temple.

436
00:27:33,410 --> 00:27:35,610
Although usually you should go in through the Nio Gate,

437
00:27:36,210 --> 00:27:38,210
this is a shortcut.

438
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:43,250
(Kurama Temple  Inner Temple  588 meters)

439
00:28:08,820 --> 00:28:11,410
(Immobile Hall of Sojyougatani)
This is the Immobile Hall of Sojyougatani.

440
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:16,110
Ushiwakamaru learned Kendo here from Tengu.

441
00:28:19,010 --> 00:28:22,210
This is really a good place for practicing kendo.

442
00:28:24,010 --> 00:28:27,710
This cedar tree is really big.

443
00:28:32,410 --> 00:28:34,410
Hattori, it's not here either.

444
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:36,310
Get down.

445
00:28:42,010 --> 00:28:42,910
Stop.

446
00:28:43,810 --> 00:28:44,510
Kudo.

447
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:01,310
This guy is just like Ushiwakamaru.

448
00:29:11,010 --> 00:29:11,510
Darn.

449
00:29:13,010 --> 00:29:14,610
Kudo, catch it. Let's go!

450
00:29:33,410 --> 00:29:34,610
Almost there!

451
00:30:04,710 --> 00:30:06,010
That's harsh.

452
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:21,530
(Kurama Temple)

453
00:30:29,750 --> 00:30:32,100
(Kurama Temple Station)

454
00:30:32,210 --> 00:30:34,410
Passengers, please get in the train as soon as possible.

455
00:30:34,710 --> 00:30:36,310
The train is about to depart.

456
00:30:38,210 --> 00:30:40,210
Don't have to be in such a hurry.

457
00:30:47,110 --> 00:30:48,210
This is a railway track.

458
00:30:48,510 --> 00:30:50,310
Don't talk to me, or I'll be distracted.

459
00:30:51,210 --> 00:30:52,610
Violation of the traffic law.

460
00:30:53,110 --> 00:30:54,310
You'll definitely get your license revoked this time.

461
00:31:06,910 --> 00:31:07,610
What is he going to do?

462
00:31:21,910 --> 00:31:22,710
Damn it.

463
00:31:23,710 --> 00:31:25,210
I literally almost caught up.

464
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:27,810
That guy should be the murderer

465
00:31:28,410 --> 00:31:31,010
who killed Genjibotaru, right?

466
00:31:31,310 --> 00:31:32,410
Probably.

467
00:31:32,810 --> 00:31:35,310
But I don't know why he attacked you.

468
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:45,310
Hattori,

469
00:31:45,410 --> 00:31:46,410
why are you here?

470
00:31:48,010 --> 00:31:49,410
I ran into Kudo on the street.

471
00:31:49,410 --> 00:31:51,410
I mean, this kid.

472
00:31:51,710 --> 00:31:54,010
And we wanted to solve the riddle in the painting together.

473
00:31:54,210 --> 00:31:57,010
So has the riddle in the painting been solved?

474
00:31:57,410 --> 00:31:59,910
Not yet, it's hard.

475
00:32:00,810 --> 00:32:02,910
By the way, did uncle solve it?

476
00:32:03,510 --> 00:32:05,240
Speaking of this,

477
00:32:07,810 --> 00:32:12,740
♪ Korekawa Chiaki on the pillow ♪

478
00:32:12,860 --> 00:32:15,820
♪ Korekawa Chiaki on the pillow ♪
(Ponto-cho)

479
00:32:17,610 --> 00:32:19,970
♪ Really miss Gion ♪
(Teahouse "Sakura House")

480
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:29,610
♪ Really miss Gion ♪
(Kayoichi Geisha)

481
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:42,710
♪ Belt hanging down ♪

482
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:51,650
(Suzu Chika, 19, Geisha)

483
00:32:58,110 --> 00:33:00,910
That's great. Ms. Suzu Chika is truly the number one in Japan.

484
00:33:01,310 --> 00:33:03,610
It's a great honor to hear that you like it.

485
00:33:04,410 --> 00:33:07,310
Then come and pour wine for Mr. Mouri.

486
00:33:07,310 --> 00:33:07,810
Right away.

487
00:33:19,610 --> 00:33:20,910
Please enjoy.

488
00:33:23,410 --> 00:33:26,810
My Mouri seems to have climbed to heaven.

489
00:33:26,910 --> 00:33:28,610
Go ahead and try to climb.

490
00:33:30,210 --> 00:33:32,510
Why are you guys here?

491
00:33:33,810 --> 00:33:36,310
The Chief Priest told us about it.

492
00:33:36,410 --> 00:33:38,810
Oh, it's the Chief Priest.

493
00:33:39,210 --> 00:33:41,710
Then would you like to join us?

494
00:33:41,810 --> 00:33:44,610
Sorry to interrupt.

495
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:53,010
Hey, aren't you from Miyagawa...

496
00:33:53,110 --> 00:33:55,910
Yes, I'm Suzu Chika.

497
00:33:56,210 --> 00:33:57,610
I owe you for that one time.

498
00:33:58,610 --> 00:34:00,310
Do you know, Heiji?

499
00:34:01,210 --> 00:34:02,210
Kind of.

500
00:34:02,510 --> 00:34:05,310
You create trouble when no one notices, seriously.

501
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:06,810
Ran,

502
00:34:07,010 --> 00:34:09,410
don't blame your father.

503
00:34:09,510 --> 00:34:11,910
I invited him to come.

504
00:34:12,110 --> 00:34:12,910
Yeah,

505
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:14,210
we wanted the renowned detective to help us

506
00:34:14,210 --> 00:34:17,610
with investigating the Genjibotaru's case together.

507
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,780
(Sakura House's owner)
Speaking of the members of Genjibotaru,

508
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:23,120
it seems that everyone has a copy of "Chronicles of Yoshitsune".

509
00:34:23,310 --> 00:34:26,910
I have one, too. It's a good book.

510
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:28,410
Right, bookstore boss?

511
00:34:28,610 --> 00:34:32,610
Yes, but I don't like that book very much.

512
00:34:32,910 --> 00:34:34,010
Although the name is "Chronicles of Yoshitsune",

513
00:34:34,010 --> 00:34:36,010
it's all about Benkei's deeds.

514
00:34:36,010 --> 00:34:37,910
It should be called "Benkeiji".

515
00:34:38,010 --> 00:34:39,710
But I like it.

516
00:34:40,010 --> 00:34:42,610
Especially Benkei's story in Ataka. That's the best.

517
00:34:42,710 --> 00:34:44,610
What is Ataka?

518
00:34:44,810 --> 00:34:47,010
It's a play of Noh theatre.

519
00:34:47,010 --> 00:34:49,410
In order to escape Yorimoto's pursuit,

520
00:34:49,610 --> 00:34:53,010
Yoshitsune and the family members disguised as monks

521
00:34:53,110 --> 00:34:55,510
to pass the checkpoint at Anzaka.

522
00:34:55,610 --> 00:34:59,310
Just when Yoshitsune's disguise was about to be seen through,

523
00:34:59,910 --> 00:35:03,910
Benkei acted within a split second and beat Yoshitsune.

524
00:35:04,710 --> 00:35:05,610
Why?

525
00:35:06,110 --> 00:35:08,510
To deceive the guards at the checkpoint.

526
00:35:08,810 --> 00:35:13,510
Because no one would have thought
that the subordinate would beat his master.

527
00:35:14,010 --> 00:35:17,710
Then Yoshitsune and his party passed the checkpoint smoothly.

528
00:35:18,210 --> 00:35:21,910
Afterwards, Benkei cried and apologized to Yoshitsune.

529
00:35:22,210 --> 00:35:25,510
Unexpectedly, Yoshitsune praised Benkei for his wit.

530
00:35:25,810 --> 00:35:28,110
From then on, the master and subordinate had a deep connection.

531
00:35:28,110 --> 00:35:29,710
And the story went on as a legend.

532
00:35:32,010 --> 00:35:35,610
I'm sorry. I've been having trouble sleeping lately.

533
00:35:35,710 --> 00:35:39,210
I want to rest for a while in the room down there.

534
00:35:39,310 --> 00:35:43,010
We don't have guests coming in tonight.

535
00:35:43,110 --> 00:35:44,410
You can go to the room next door.

536
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:47,410
It's alright. The room down there will do.

537
00:35:48,010 --> 00:35:51,210
Please wake me up at 9 o'clock.

538
00:35:52,810 --> 00:35:55,310
Everyone, please have fun.

539
00:36:03,210 --> 00:36:04,510
We can see the river.

540
00:36:04,910 --> 00:36:06,110
It's Kamogawa.

541
00:36:06,510 --> 00:36:08,310
The cherry blossoms are so beautiful.

542
00:36:08,710 --> 00:36:09,610
Yeah.

543
00:36:10,410 --> 00:36:12,010
Ran, come and have a look.

544
00:36:12,710 --> 00:36:16,610
It's nice to view cherry blossom in pairs on the Kamogawa River,

545
00:36:16,910 --> 00:36:22,110
but enjoying the cherry blossoms across the Misogi River
that surrounds this building

546
00:36:22,110 --> 00:36:23,610
also feels quite special.

547
00:36:24,210 --> 00:36:25,710
Yeah, really beautiful.

548
00:36:25,710 --> 00:36:27,610
It is good indeed.

549
00:36:28,310 --> 00:36:30,510
It's almost like a delicacy.

550
00:36:30,810 --> 00:36:32,010
I really want to eat it.

551
00:36:35,810 --> 00:36:37,310
Are you hurt?

552
00:36:37,410 --> 00:36:39,010
Yeah, a little bit.

553
00:36:39,510 --> 00:36:41,710
Let me help you.

554
00:36:42,010 --> 00:36:43,410
That's too much.

555
00:36:45,010 --> 00:36:46,510
Creepy old man.

556
00:36:47,010 --> 00:36:48,810
Hey, look.

557
00:36:51,410 --> 00:36:52,710
Inspector Ayanokoji.

558
00:36:53,010 --> 00:36:55,110
What is he doing there?

559
00:36:55,610 --> 00:36:57,910
You can go to the terrace below

560
00:36:57,910 --> 00:36:59,710
to see the cherry blossoms at night.

561
00:37:00,110 --> 00:37:02,110
After the clouds clear tonight,

562
00:37:02,110 --> 00:37:04,010
the moon will show its beauty.

563
00:37:04,410 --> 00:37:05,310
Let's go and check it out.

564
00:37:05,910 --> 00:37:06,810
Great.

565
00:37:07,310 --> 00:37:09,110
I'll stay here.

566
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:10,110
Me, too.

567
00:37:10,110 --> 00:37:11,110
Why?

568
00:37:11,610 --> 00:37:13,710
Do you care about that geisha?

569
00:37:13,710 --> 00:37:16,310
Idiot, what nonsense are you talking about?

570
00:37:28,110 --> 00:37:29,110
I lost.

571
00:37:29,510 --> 00:37:31,910
Uncle is really going all out.

572
00:37:31,910 --> 00:37:34,010
He has always been like this.

573
00:37:34,010 --> 00:37:35,610
Suzu Chika, one more time.

574
00:37:35,610 --> 00:37:37,210
Do it again.

575
00:37:37,210 --> 00:37:38,310
I'd like to use the restroom.

576
00:37:39,210 --> 00:37:41,310
It's okay. I'm not drunk yet.

577
00:37:41,710 --> 00:37:43,110
Just stay with Mr. Mouri.

578
00:37:43,110 --> 00:37:43,910
OK.

579
00:37:44,310 --> 00:37:45,910
Okay, let's start.

580
00:37:48,210 --> 00:37:49,610
The moon is out.

581
00:37:54,810 --> 00:37:55,510
The moon.

582
00:37:57,110 --> 00:37:57,710
What's wrong?

583
00:37:59,210 --> 00:38:02,410
It reminds me of the date I had with Ran before.

584
00:38:03,110 --> 00:38:05,210
That day, when I remembered I had a date,

585
00:38:05,810 --> 00:38:07,510
I was already two hours late.

586
00:38:07,510 --> 00:38:08,810
That's too crazy.

587
00:38:09,410 --> 00:38:12,610
I thought she had left.

588
00:38:13,010 --> 00:38:15,710
But I still went to our meet-up point to check.

589
00:38:26,710 --> 00:38:27,210
Who is it?

590
00:38:33,810 --> 00:38:37,010
I'm sorry, I totally...

591
00:38:37,410 --> 00:38:38,410
It's great.

592
00:38:38,910 --> 00:38:39,810
I was worried that

593
00:38:39,810 --> 00:38:42,510
something might've happened to you.

594
00:38:49,010 --> 00:38:50,210
Was that when you realized

595
00:38:50,510 --> 00:38:54,310
that she's more than a childhood friend?

596
00:38:54,710 --> 00:38:57,310
Idiot, there is no such thing.

597
00:38:59,310 --> 00:39:01,410
I have long discovered that she's more than a childhood friend.

598
00:39:03,710 --> 00:39:07,110
She's probably still waiting for me.

599
00:39:11,010 --> 00:39:12,310
What's wrong, Ran?

600
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:14,910
Nothing.

601
00:39:17,810 --> 00:39:20,810
Heiji is really irritating.

602
00:39:21,010 --> 00:39:24,010
But Toyama, I'm so jealous of you.

603
00:39:24,810 --> 00:39:28,410
Because you can see each other when you want to.

604
00:39:29,910 --> 00:39:31,210
Ran.

605
00:39:31,810 --> 00:39:36,110
Yes, I rarely get to see Kyogoku, too.

606
00:39:36,910 --> 00:39:39,010
The troubles of girls are endless.

607
00:39:40,410 --> 00:39:44,610
In comparison, the uncles are really energetic.

608
00:40:12,110 --> 00:40:14,610
Mr. Sakura, it's 9 o'clock.

609
00:40:14,910 --> 00:40:15,810
Mr. Sakura.

610
00:40:16,810 --> 00:40:17,710
Please excuse me.

611
00:40:19,810 --> 00:40:21,110
Where did he go?

612
00:40:25,910 --> 00:40:26,810
That's strange.

613
00:40:36,210 --> 00:40:37,310
Mr. Sakura?

614
00:40:49,610 --> 00:40:51,310
What's with the scream just now?

615
00:40:51,910 --> 00:40:53,010
Someone, help!

616
00:40:55,410 --> 00:40:56,410
What's wrong?

617
00:40:57,010 --> 00:40:58,410
Mr. Sakura…

618
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:04,910
Mr. Sakura…

619
00:41:05,410 --> 00:41:07,410
No one is allowed in.

620
00:41:07,510 --> 00:41:09,310
Ran, call the police.

621
00:41:09,610 --> 00:41:10,110
Sure.

622
00:41:12,010 --> 00:41:15,110
The carotid artery was slashed with a sharp weapon.

623
00:41:15,510 --> 00:41:16,710
The cut is perfect.

624
00:41:17,010 --> 00:41:19,810
Should be the same murderer as the serial-killer case.

625
00:41:20,310 --> 00:41:23,010
I keep thinking that I've met you somewhere.

626
00:41:23,510 --> 00:41:24,210
Are you the junior detective,

627
00:41:24,810 --> 00:41:25,910
Heiji Hattori?

628
00:41:26,210 --> 00:41:27,010
Yes.

629
00:41:27,510 --> 00:41:31,110
Before the police arrive, please wait in your rooms.

630
00:41:31,710 --> 00:41:33,910
Do not come out.

631
00:41:35,110 --> 00:41:36,210
Got it.

632
00:41:40,210 --> 00:41:41,210
Mr. Sakura seems to have gotten killed

633
00:41:41,710 --> 00:41:45,810
while looking for something in the warehouse.

634
00:41:45,910 --> 00:41:47,410
What was he looking for?

635
00:41:49,110 --> 00:41:51,610
The button of the coat got torn off,

636
00:41:53,210 --> 00:41:54,610
probably because there were gloves on

637
00:41:54,610 --> 00:41:56,710
so it'd be too much trouble to unbutton it.

638
00:41:56,710 --> 00:41:59,710
But the wallet filled with money is still here,

639
00:42:00,510 --> 00:42:02,310
so it's not for money.

640
00:42:04,810 --> 00:42:06,510
Don't touch the body.

641
00:42:06,510 --> 00:42:08,510
How many times do I have to say this for you to understand?

642
00:42:10,210 --> 00:42:11,910
Ouch!

643
00:42:16,810 --> 00:42:18,710
I'm Ayanokoji from the Kyoto Police Department.

644
00:42:19,410 --> 00:42:21,810
Thank you for your hard work. Please come in.

645
00:42:22,910 --> 00:42:24,010
You guard the door.

646
00:42:24,010 --> 00:42:24,710
Roger that.

647
00:42:27,810 --> 00:42:29,410
Isn't this a police officer in Kyoto?

648
00:42:30,010 --> 00:42:31,710
You got here so fast.

649
00:42:34,210 --> 00:42:36,410
Where's your chipmunk?

650
00:42:37,710 --> 00:42:39,910
I don't always take it with me.

651
00:42:41,210 --> 00:42:44,010
What do you think? Did someone outside do it?

652
00:42:44,410 --> 00:42:46,110
We can't eliminate the possibility,

653
00:42:46,510 --> 00:42:48,810
but if the door was opened and made a sound,

654
00:42:48,810 --> 00:42:50,210
the owner would have noticed,

655
00:42:50,910 --> 00:42:51,910
Besides,

656
00:42:52,410 --> 00:42:53,510
the murderer knew that Mr. Sakura

657
00:42:54,010 --> 00:42:57,110
would go to the warehouse for some reason.

658
00:42:57,710 --> 00:42:58,310
In other words,

659
00:42:58,910 --> 00:43:00,510
he probably knew Mr. Sakura,

660
00:43:00,810 --> 00:43:05,410
Saijo, Ryuen, Mizuo and the others.

661
00:43:06,510 --> 00:43:07,910
The three of them

662
00:43:07,910 --> 00:43:10,410
have been to the bathroom

663
00:43:10,710 --> 00:43:12,610
after Mr. Sakura and Ran left.

664
00:43:12,610 --> 00:43:16,110
There is also a staircase leading to the basement next to it.

665
00:43:16,610 --> 00:43:19,210
This means that the three could have gone
to the warehouse and killed Mr. Sakura

666
00:43:19,810 --> 00:43:24,210
when they pretended to go to the bathroom.

667
00:43:26,410 --> 00:43:28,310
But one thing feels out of place.

668
00:43:28,810 --> 00:43:30,610
Why did Suzu Chika go with Mizuo

669
00:43:30,910 --> 00:43:32,910
to the bathroom?

670
00:43:34,610 --> 00:43:36,610
The geishas seem to do that.

671
00:43:37,010 --> 00:43:40,910
But she didn't do that with Ryuen and Saijo.

672
00:43:41,210 --> 00:43:43,710
That's because she happened to be playing a game with my uncle.

673
00:43:44,110 --> 00:43:45,110
We can also say that

674
00:43:45,510 --> 00:43:48,310
they might have specifically picked that time to go to the bathroom.

675
00:43:48,310 --> 00:43:49,610
If that's the case,

676
00:43:50,210 --> 00:43:52,110
the murderer is either Ryuen or Saijo.

677
00:43:52,510 --> 00:43:54,110
If Suzu Chika is not an accomplice,

678
00:43:54,110 --> 00:43:56,510
then Mizuo should be innocent.

679
00:43:59,110 --> 00:43:59,810
Yes.

680
00:44:00,710 --> 00:44:01,710
Then let's go.

681
00:44:02,810 --> 00:44:04,110
Stop pretending.

682
00:44:05,010 --> 00:44:07,810
Did you find something in Mr. Sakura's upper pocket?

683
00:44:09,410 --> 00:44:10,210
Well.

684
00:44:11,410 --> 00:44:14,410
Mr. Sakura's shop should be on Teramachi Street, right?

685
00:44:15,410 --> 00:44:17,970
(Sakura Antique Shop)

686
00:44:26,410 --> 00:44:27,510
Gikeki.

687
00:44:30,210 --> 00:44:31,410
Iseno Saburo.

688
00:44:32,010 --> 00:44:32,910
Hattori.

689
00:44:36,910 --> 00:44:40,410
What? Mr. Sakura is Iseno Saburo?

690
00:44:42,210 --> 00:44:42,910
What is this?

691
00:44:44,410 --> 00:44:45,010
This is...

692
00:44:45,710 --> 00:44:46,910
a copy of the painting.

693
00:44:47,610 --> 00:44:48,910
What is going on?

694
00:44:49,210 --> 00:44:52,010
Mr. Sakura also had this painting, which means

695
00:44:52,710 --> 00:44:56,310
the letter was sent by Mr. Sakura to Sannou Temple.

696
00:44:57,410 --> 00:44:59,610
But for what?

697
00:45:01,010 --> 00:45:01,610
What?

698
00:45:02,210 --> 00:45:04,110
Mr. Sakura was Iseno Saburo.

699
00:45:04,110 --> 00:45:07,610
Yes, it looks like he was a member of Genjibotaru.

700
00:45:08,210 --> 00:45:11,210
Wait a minute, the one who got killed is...

701
00:45:12,010 --> 00:45:15,610
Could the next one be me, the one they missed?

702
00:45:17,810 --> 00:45:20,010
If this is the case, it should've happened a long time ago.

703
00:45:21,910 --> 00:45:23,710
If the painting in Mr. Sakura's house

704
00:45:23,710 --> 00:45:25,410
is a copy of the original,

705
00:45:25,410 --> 00:45:27,610
wouldn't it be very likely that Mr. Sakura
carried the original with him

706
00:45:27,610 --> 00:45:30,210
and it got taken away by the murderer?

707
00:45:30,210 --> 00:45:31,210
I see.

708
00:45:31,910 --> 00:45:36,110
The murderer didn't expect Mr. Sakura to keep a copy in advance.

709
00:45:36,110 --> 00:45:38,810
So who is the murderer?

710
00:45:39,410 --> 00:45:42,110
I think the murderer is among Mr. Ryuen, Mr. Saijo.

711
00:45:42,110 --> 00:45:45,010
Mr. Mizuo and Ms. Suzu Chika.

712
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:49,310
But none of them had a weapon with them.

713
00:45:49,310 --> 00:45:51,710
After the two of you left,

714
00:45:51,710 --> 00:45:53,610
the police did a search.

715
00:45:54,510 --> 00:45:55,410
How could someone still carry a weapon

716
00:45:55,410 --> 00:45:58,010
after killing someone?

717
00:45:58,410 --> 00:46:00,910
It must have been thrown away or hidden.

718
00:46:01,210 --> 00:46:04,510
But it wasn't found in the store either.

719
00:46:04,510 --> 00:46:05,810
How about the Misogi River?

720
00:46:06,410 --> 00:46:09,610
Could it be thrown out of the glass window in the basement?

721
00:46:09,610 --> 00:46:12,910
Right? I think so, too.

722
00:46:14,210 --> 00:46:15,610
Suzuki said she heard

723
00:46:15,610 --> 00:46:19,210
the sound of something falling into the Misogi River.

724
00:46:19,210 --> 00:46:20,110
Really?

725
00:46:20,110 --> 00:46:25,110
Yes, but the police searched the river

726
00:46:25,410 --> 00:46:27,110
and found nothing.

727
00:46:27,610 --> 00:46:30,010
That's strange.

728
00:46:30,410 --> 00:46:32,110
In this case, there must be an accomplice.

729
00:46:32,510 --> 00:46:35,810
The accomplice outside picked up the murder weapon from the river.

730
00:46:35,810 --> 00:46:37,610
This is impossible.

731
00:46:38,610 --> 00:46:41,510
Why? Ku…Conan.

732
00:46:42,210 --> 00:46:44,810
It's a full moon tonight, so it's very bright outside.

733
00:46:45,310 --> 00:46:49,810
The balcony floor has a gap that allows one to see the river below.

734
00:46:50,210 --> 00:46:52,910
If there is an accomplice over there,

735
00:46:52,910 --> 00:46:55,510
Ran-chan and the others should've noticed.

736
00:46:56,410 --> 00:46:57,710
That's true.

737
00:46:57,710 --> 00:46:59,210
The truth is,

738
00:46:59,610 --> 00:47:01,510
the murderer is someone outside.

739
00:47:01,610 --> 00:47:04,210
Before Ran and the others got to the balcony,

740
00:47:04,410 --> 00:47:06,610
the murderer went in from the glass window downstairs,

741
00:47:07,110 --> 00:47:09,310
hid in a place somewhere like the bathroom,

742
00:47:10,010 --> 00:47:13,810
killed Mr. Sakura while he came in looking for something,

743
00:47:14,310 --> 00:47:18,910
and then ran away with the murder weapon through the glass window.

744
00:47:19,210 --> 00:47:21,810
But none of us saw anyone suspicious.

745
00:47:22,510 --> 00:47:25,010
There are no witnesses by the riverbank either.

746
00:47:25,110 --> 00:47:26,410
It's a coincidence.

747
00:47:27,210 --> 00:47:28,810
The murderer had better luck.

748
00:47:30,110 --> 00:47:32,110
I feel like something's not right.

749
00:48:04,310 --> 00:48:05,910
That guy is from Mount Kurama...

750
00:48:19,610 --> 00:48:21,510
Toyama, don't let go!

751
00:48:21,510 --> 00:48:22,710
What?

752
00:48:35,410 --> 00:48:37,210
Stay here, okay?

753
00:48:38,810 --> 00:48:39,510
Heiji!

754
00:48:56,810 --> 00:49:00,110
Do you want to have a showdown with me? That works.

755
00:49:04,610 --> 00:49:06,110
What? There are flaws everywhere.

756
00:49:11,010 --> 00:49:12,410
Wearing a wristband.

757
00:49:29,810 --> 00:49:32,410
Are you the murderer who killed Mr. Sakura?

758
00:49:32,810 --> 00:49:36,410
Then try it here just like back then.

759
00:50:10,710 --> 00:50:12,910
This is not what you want.

760
00:50:14,710 --> 00:50:15,910
I can't see clearly anymore.

761
00:50:29,010 --> 00:50:30,810
Inspector, here!

762
00:50:39,710 --> 00:50:41,310
Heiji! Are you okay?

763
00:50:41,510 --> 00:50:43,710
Toyama, where's the police?

764
00:50:44,010 --> 00:50:45,910
It was obviously a bluff.

765
00:50:46,810 --> 00:50:49,510
Where did you learn this?

766
00:50:50,110 --> 00:50:52,110
What a terrible woman.

767
00:50:53,210 --> 00:50:53,910
Heiji.

768
00:50:58,550 --> 00:51:00,490
(Umekouji Hospital)

769
00:51:04,710 --> 00:51:06,710
Heiji, you're awake.

770
00:51:06,710 --> 00:51:07,910
Toyama.

771
00:51:08,210 --> 00:51:09,410
Thank God.

772
00:51:09,410 --> 00:51:11,310
Worried us to death, Heiji.

773
00:51:13,210 --> 00:51:14,310
Inspector Otaki.

774
00:51:14,710 --> 00:51:16,910
And, who are you again?

775
00:51:17,910 --> 00:51:20,110
I am Shiratori from the Police Department.

776
00:51:20,110 --> 00:51:24,110
I heard that Shozo Sakura who got killed was a member of Genjibotaru,

777
00:51:24,110 --> 00:51:25,810
so I rushed over from Tokyo.

778
00:51:26,810 --> 00:51:27,810
Does it still hurt?

779
00:51:28,410 --> 00:51:29,310
A little.

780
00:51:29,610 --> 00:51:34,810
The stolen art was found in Sakura's shop.

781
00:51:35,410 --> 00:51:37,110
Are you awake?

782
00:51:37,610 --> 00:51:39,510
Inspector, where's the short knife?

783
00:51:39,610 --> 00:51:41,510
It's going under tests.

784
00:51:42,110 --> 00:51:44,410
Tell me immediately when the result comes out.

785
00:51:44,510 --> 00:51:46,610
If the evidence is not enough,

786
00:51:47,410 --> 00:51:49,610
you can use the wound on my shoulder as well.

787
00:51:50,110 --> 00:51:51,610
What evidence?

788
00:51:52,710 --> 00:51:54,010
The evidence to prove that the short knife

789
00:51:54,010 --> 00:51:56,910
is the murder weapon that killed Mr. Sakura.

790
00:51:57,410 --> 00:51:58,710
Actually, it'll be great if someone had come into contact

791
00:51:58,710 --> 00:52:01,110
with the murderer's skin.

792
00:52:02,110 --> 00:52:05,110
What about the motorcycle? Isn't there a motorcycle?

793
00:52:05,110 --> 00:52:06,810
That was a stolen one.

794
00:52:06,810 --> 00:52:08,910
The evidence to find the murderer.

795
00:52:12,210 --> 00:52:17,310
Also, do you understand what this painting means now?

796
00:52:17,610 --> 00:52:20,610
It was tuck into Mr. Sakura's "Chronicles of Yoshitsune".

797
00:52:22,210 --> 00:52:23,310
Are you sure you don't know?

798
00:52:24,710 --> 00:52:26,110
Don't worry then.

799
00:52:31,010 --> 00:52:33,610
Just stay put then.

800
00:52:35,110 --> 00:52:36,410
I'll be going as well.

801
00:52:37,510 --> 00:52:38,910
Take care and feel better soon, Heiji.

802
00:52:44,510 --> 00:52:46,810
I'll give dad a call.

803
00:52:49,210 --> 00:52:50,810
Let me ask the doctor for you.

804
00:52:52,710 --> 00:52:54,010
Conan is with me.

805
00:52:54,010 --> 00:52:54,910
Ran.

806
00:52:54,910 --> 00:52:58,010
I'll go out for a bit. please take care of Heiji.

807
00:53:10,310 --> 00:53:13,210
Is it okay? Why don't you stay in the hospital to recover?

808
00:53:13,210 --> 00:53:14,410
It's okay.

809
00:53:14,410 --> 00:53:16,810
But that guy is really strange.

810
00:53:17,610 --> 00:53:19,410
I've never seen that kind of swordsmanship.

811
00:53:19,710 --> 00:53:23,010
He might have added steel bars to the wristband.

812
00:53:23,810 --> 00:53:27,310
I wanted to use the wound to find the murder weapon.

813
00:53:27,310 --> 00:53:30,110
That's why I got myself a cut by the short knife.

814
00:53:30,110 --> 00:53:32,310
I didn't expect him to drop the knife.

815
00:53:32,410 --> 00:53:33,410
Why is that?

816
00:53:33,910 --> 00:53:35,210
Also,

817
00:53:35,210 --> 00:53:38,010
while we were fighting,

818
00:53:38,010 --> 00:53:41,210
the guy actually wanted to pick up this sachet that I dropped.

819
00:53:41,310 --> 00:53:43,610
All things that one can't figure out.

820
00:53:43,710 --> 00:53:45,010
Could the one wearing an old man's mask

821
00:53:45,510 --> 00:53:47,510
be your first love?

822
00:53:48,210 --> 00:53:49,510
You have a point.

823
00:53:50,610 --> 00:53:51,610
How could there be such a thing?

824
00:53:51,840 --> 00:53:54,130
(Mizuo's House)

825
00:53:54,710 --> 00:53:57,010
You were attacked later.

826
00:53:57,510 --> 00:53:59,110
I'm sorry but,

827
00:53:59,610 --> 00:54:01,710
I wanted to ask about Mr. Mizuo's alibi.

828
00:54:01,810 --> 00:54:05,210
The murderer wore the mask of the old man in Noh theatre.

829
00:54:05,310 --> 00:54:06,410
Old man's mask.

830
00:54:06,910 --> 00:54:08,610
Also, Mr. Saijo

831
00:54:08,710 --> 00:54:11,410
and Mr. Ryuen's alibis would be greatly appreciated as well.

832
00:54:12,010 --> 00:54:13,110
We have to be questioned, too?

833
00:54:13,210 --> 00:54:14,310
Seriously?

834
00:54:14,610 --> 00:54:16,810
I came here today to talk about the murderer of Mr. Sakura

835
00:54:17,110 --> 00:54:21,210
with Suzu Chika in a party of four.

836
00:54:21,410 --> 00:54:22,310
Right?

837
00:54:23,810 --> 00:54:28,110
It's okay. I went straight home to sleep right after yesterday.

838
00:54:28,510 --> 00:54:30,410
But I'm still single,

839
00:54:31,010 --> 00:54:33,210
and my room is far from my mom's room.

840
00:54:33,410 --> 00:54:36,910
I can't prove whether I've been at home all that time.

841
00:54:37,210 --> 00:54:39,310
Same here.

842
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:43,210
I live alone on the second floor of the store on Teramachi Street.

843
00:54:43,510 --> 00:54:45,110
After I returned to the temple,

844
00:54:45,110 --> 00:54:49,010
I read the scriptures in the main hall for a while.
Then I fell asleep.

845
00:54:49,610 --> 00:54:50,810
No witnesses.

846
00:54:51,010 --> 00:54:51,910
I see.

847
00:54:52,910 --> 00:54:53,710
I have another question.

848
00:54:54,210 --> 00:54:56,410
Has anyone practiced archery?

849
00:54:56,810 --> 00:54:58,610
Archery? No.

850
00:54:58,610 --> 00:55:02,910
I once used a Catalpa Bow for the Noh play called
"Appreciating the Fallen Leaves".

851
00:55:03,410 --> 00:55:08,610
I once used the bow and arrow to disperse evil spirits.

852
00:55:08,910 --> 00:55:14,210
So was there anyone in the tea house that knew archery?

853
00:55:14,810 --> 00:55:16,910
Sounds like Yamakura.

854
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:20,500
Does that Yamakura use bow and arrows?

855
00:55:20,680 --> 00:55:22,840
(Tae Yamakura)
But she wasn't present at the time.

856
00:55:22,840 --> 00:55:23,310
But she wasn't present at the time

857
00:55:23,410 --> 00:55:24,410
Oh no...

858
00:55:25,710 --> 00:55:26,910
Excuse me.

859
00:55:27,210 --> 00:55:28,310
She is coming.

860
00:55:29,310 --> 00:55:30,110
What?

861
00:55:30,110 --> 00:55:30,810
What's wrong?

862
00:55:31,110 --> 00:55:32,010
Please.

863
00:55:32,710 --> 00:55:34,210
Are you Miss Suzu Chika?

864
00:55:34,310 --> 00:55:35,710
Yes.

865
00:55:35,810 --> 00:55:38,610
You must be surprised by how different she looks.

866
00:55:39,110 --> 00:55:39,910
Please come in.

867
00:55:40,910 --> 00:55:42,510
OK, thanks.

868
00:55:54,210 --> 00:55:56,110
Thanks for visiting last night.

869
00:55:56,110 --> 00:55:57,710
Please come back again.

870
00:55:57,910 --> 00:55:59,410
Don't mention it.

871
00:56:02,510 --> 00:56:04,110
Thanks, bye.

872
00:56:05,510 --> 00:56:08,310
Sannou Temple is on Rokkaku street.

873
00:56:08,510 --> 00:56:10,710
This is Ebisu Avenue.

874
00:56:10,810 --> 00:56:14,310
Maru-Take-Ebisu-Ni-Oshi-Oike

875
00:56:14,810 --> 00:56:16,610
Ane-San-Rokkaku…

876
00:56:16,610 --> 00:56:19,210
So it should be the sixth street.

877
00:56:21,310 --> 00:56:26,110
Maru-Take-Ebisu-Ni-Oshi-Oike

878
00:56:27,410 --> 00:56:29,210
What's the song you just sang now?

879
00:56:29,310 --> 00:56:32,810
We call it the Temari song.

880
00:56:34,510 --> 00:56:36,510
It's a song made up with all the major roads
in Kyoto that run east to west

881
00:56:36,510 --> 00:56:39,110
appearing in the order of north to south.

882
00:56:39,610 --> 00:56:43,710
Maru-Take-Ebisu-Ni-Oshi-Oike

883
00:56:44,010 --> 00:56:48,210
Ane-San-Rokkaku-Tako-Nishiki

884
00:56:48,610 --> 00:56:52,910
Shi-Aya-Butsu-Taka-Matsu-Man-Gojo

885
00:56:53,110 --> 00:56:56,610
Setta-Chara, chara-Uonotana

886
00:56:57,010 --> 00:57:01,010
through Rokujo-Santetsu

887
00:57:01,210 --> 00:57:05,510
after Shichijo comes Hachi-Kujo

888
00:57:05,710 --> 00:57:10,210
Kujo, toji comes at the end

889
00:57:11,410 --> 00:57:12,610
Kids in Kyoto

890
00:57:12,810 --> 00:57:16,110
all sing this song to remember the names of the streets in Kyoto.

891
00:57:17,310 --> 00:57:20,210
Then you are also from Kyoto.

892
00:57:20,810 --> 00:57:21,910
Yes.

893
00:57:22,210 --> 00:57:22,610
How old are you?

894
00:57:22,810 --> 00:57:23,910
19 years old.

895
00:57:24,310 --> 00:57:24,910
19.

896
00:57:30,710 --> 00:57:32,810
Then this is Oike Street.

897
00:57:33,210 --> 00:57:35,010
I'll be going.

898
00:57:36,810 --> 00:57:37,810
Goodbye.

899
00:57:38,110 --> 00:57:38,910
Goodbye.

900
00:57:40,410 --> 00:57:42,010
Are you thinking that she is…

901
00:57:42,210 --> 00:57:43,410
Absolutely right.

902
00:57:43,810 --> 00:57:46,910
She was born in Kyoto and is two years older than me.

903
00:57:47,210 --> 00:57:50,310
But don't the kids in Kyoto all sing that song?

904
00:57:50,610 --> 00:57:52,410
I've reunited with her at last.

905
00:57:54,010 --> 00:57:54,910
Hey.

906
00:57:55,110 --> 00:57:56,510
Heiji, what are you doing?

907
00:57:56,710 --> 00:57:59,210
It's ridiculous to leave the hospital like this.

908
00:57:59,810 --> 00:58:00,810
Officer Otaki.

909
00:58:01,210 --> 00:58:02,610
(Kyoto Prefecture Police)
Let's not talk about this yet.

910
00:58:02,910 --> 00:58:05,010
(Kyoto Prefecture Police)
The results of the blood test came out.

911
00:58:05,010 --> 00:58:05,310
The result of the blood test came out.

912
00:58:05,710 --> 00:58:07,310
The blood on the handle of the short knife

913
00:58:07,310 --> 00:58:12,610
is found to be of the same blood type as that of Mr. Sakura's.

914
00:58:12,910 --> 00:58:17,310
The marks that the sword left are the same as
the marks on Sakura's body as well.

915
00:58:17,510 --> 00:58:18,310
Really?

916
00:58:18,410 --> 00:58:20,710
Heiji, I've told you the results.

917
00:58:20,910 --> 00:58:22,610
But don't you mess around.

918
00:58:22,810 --> 00:58:24,910
If anything happens to you,

919
00:58:24,910 --> 00:58:26,310
I won't know what to say to your dad...

920
00:58:26,910 --> 00:58:27,810
I got it.

921
00:58:28,110 --> 00:58:29,710
Thank you, Inspector Otaki.

922
00:58:35,610 --> 00:58:38,210
So it seems that the person who attacked me

923
00:58:38,510 --> 00:58:41,810
is the murderer who killed Mr. Sakura.

924
00:58:42,110 --> 00:58:48,910
So those four people who couldn't get rid of
the weapon couldn't be the murderer.

925
00:59:04,210 --> 00:59:07,010
Conan, what are you doing?

926
00:59:08,210 --> 00:59:09,610
Why are you guys here?

927
00:59:09,910 --> 00:59:11,510
We solved the riddle of the Doctor,

928
00:59:11,710 --> 00:59:13,410
so he brought us to Kyoto.

929
00:59:13,610 --> 00:59:15,310
But Genta

930
00:59:15,510 --> 00:59:17,110
got lost.

931
00:59:18,310 --> 00:59:20,510
Then use the detective badge.

932
00:59:20,910 --> 00:59:23,610
I've called him, and we've been in touch,

933
00:59:23,910 --> 00:59:26,510
but Genta doesn't understand Kanji characters

934
00:59:26,710 --> 00:59:28,610
so he can't tell us where he is now.

935
00:59:29,010 --> 00:59:32,410
So I wanted to use your glasses to find him.

936
00:59:32,710 --> 00:59:35,110
OK, leave it to me.

937
00:59:38,210 --> 00:59:40,310
This is interesting, there.

938
00:59:41,110 --> 00:59:42,010
Yeah.

939
00:59:53,210 --> 00:59:55,710
There seems to be a case in your area, too.

940
00:59:55,810 --> 00:59:58,810
Yes, I will tell you the details later.

941
01:00:00,010 --> 01:00:02,710
Wait a minute, Ai, give me the medicine.

942
01:00:08,710 --> 01:00:09,710
What's that?

943
01:00:09,810 --> 01:00:11,810
Hunger suppressing medicine.

944
01:00:11,910 --> 01:00:14,810
It's developed by the doctor for those
attending wedding and funeral banquets.

945
01:00:15,010 --> 01:00:17,310
For those who can't drink,

946
01:00:17,310 --> 01:00:20,310
there's a medication that turns one's face red immediately.

947
01:00:20,310 --> 01:00:21,910
For those who want to take time off,

948
01:00:21,910 --> 01:00:26,010
there's a medication that shows symptoms
of a bad cold immediately after taking it.

949
01:00:26,210 --> 01:00:29,110
These are all developed by Ai.

950
01:00:29,310 --> 01:00:30,710
So these are useless.

951
01:00:31,420 --> 01:00:34,710
(Rokkaku Temple)
It's here. This is Rokkaku.

952
01:00:35,510 --> 01:00:37,010
He's here!

953
01:00:37,910 --> 01:00:38,810
Great!

954
01:00:39,610 --> 01:00:40,610
Mother.

955
01:00:40,610 --> 01:00:42,210
Genta is there.

956
01:00:43,710 --> 01:00:45,110
I'm saved!

957
01:00:45,110 --> 01:00:46,910
Great, Genta!

958
01:00:46,910 --> 01:00:49,510
I thought I would never see you again in my lifetime!

959
01:00:49,510 --> 01:00:50,310
Me, too.

960
01:00:50,610 --> 01:00:52,510
But this thing is really convenient,

961
01:00:54,110 --> 01:00:57,010
the badge with a signal sensor.

962
01:00:57,010 --> 01:00:57,810
Yeah!

963
01:00:58,010 --> 01:01:02,510
The frequency of the signal from this transmitter
is the same as that of the glasses.

964
01:01:03,610 --> 01:01:04,610
Hattori.

965
01:01:04,610 --> 01:01:05,710
I see.

966
01:01:05,910 --> 01:01:07,210
What's up?

967
01:01:07,510 --> 01:01:10,010
Kudo, could it be?

968
01:01:18,210 --> 01:01:19,710
It must be.

969
01:01:19,910 --> 01:01:20,510
Yes.

970
01:01:20,910 --> 01:01:25,710
What the lady heard was indeed the sound
of the murder weapon falling into the river.

971
01:01:26,010 --> 01:01:29,310
So the murderer is indeed one of those four people.

972
01:01:29,310 --> 01:01:30,810
No, one of those three.

973
01:01:31,310 --> 01:01:34,710
How could my first love be a murderer?

974
01:01:34,710 --> 01:01:36,210
Here we go again.

975
01:01:36,210 --> 01:01:38,810
But there is still something I find strange.

976
01:01:39,010 --> 01:01:44,110
The song I just heard is different from the one I remember.

977
01:01:44,710 --> 01:01:46,410
My first love

978
01:01:46,510 --> 01:01:50,210
sang "Yome-san-Rokkaku" instead of "Ane-san-Rokkaku".

979
01:01:51,310 --> 01:01:53,210
Why is that?

980
01:01:53,410 --> 01:01:54,710
How would I know?

981
01:02:08,610 --> 01:02:11,010
Found it! The broken pieces of the mask.

982
01:02:21,710 --> 01:02:22,410
Police Department,

983
01:02:23,210 --> 01:02:24,910
What are you thinking?

984
01:02:25,210 --> 01:02:26,110
Is it this one?

985
01:02:27,110 --> 01:02:30,910
Things worn on the three people killed in Tokyo.

986
01:02:31,110 --> 01:02:33,210
One was wearing a hat; one was wearing a scarf.

987
01:02:33,210 --> 01:02:35,110
And another was wearing gloves.

988
01:02:35,410 --> 01:02:37,810
The colors, styles, and textures are the same.

989
01:02:38,010 --> 01:02:39,910
Don't you think it's weird?

990
01:02:40,410 --> 01:02:41,710
Really strange.

991
01:02:42,110 --> 01:02:43,410
What's weird?

992
01:02:43,410 --> 01:02:49,410
For example, if Shiratori wore these three
by himself, then it'd feel normal.

993
01:02:49,710 --> 01:02:51,610
But if Inspector Megure wore this hat,

994
01:02:51,710 --> 01:02:53,410
and I wore this scarf,

995
01:02:53,410 --> 01:02:55,710
then Takagi wore these gloves,

996
01:02:55,710 --> 01:02:56,910
wouldn't you think it's weird?

997
01:02:57,110 --> 01:02:58,410
Indeed.

998
01:02:58,910 --> 01:03:01,210
It literally feels like Shiratori was dead,

999
01:03:01,210 --> 01:03:04,010
and the three of us divided his belongings.

1000
01:03:05,110 --> 01:03:06,210
That's it.

1001
01:03:07,010 --> 01:03:08,410
What's going on?

1002
01:03:11,210 --> 01:03:12,410
I'm hungry.

1003
01:03:12,410 --> 01:03:14,010
Bear with it.

1004
01:03:14,210 --> 01:03:18,010
Suzu Chika's mom worked as a geisha in Miyagawa.

1005
01:03:18,010 --> 01:03:20,210
She died of an illness when Suzu Chika was five years old.

1006
01:03:20,910 --> 01:03:22,810
And she was a single mother.

1007
01:03:23,310 --> 01:03:27,310
Later, Suzu Chika was adopted by the teahouse owner, Yamakura,

1008
01:03:27,310 --> 01:03:28,610
and she was raised by Yamakura.

1009
01:03:29,010 --> 01:03:31,110
What does a single mother mean?

1010
01:03:31,110 --> 01:03:32,410
I was wondering the same thing.

1011
01:03:32,410 --> 01:03:36,110
A woman who gives birth to a child without getting married?

1012
01:03:36,610 --> 01:03:39,510
Although I don't know who her father is,

1013
01:03:39,510 --> 01:03:43,110
there was money sent to her anonymously every month.

1014
01:03:43,210 --> 01:03:48,110
But for some reason it suddenly stopped three months ago.

1015
01:03:49,310 --> 01:03:52,910
It is quite perplexing indeed.

1016
01:03:53,010 --> 01:03:55,010
Three months ago?

1017
01:03:55,810 --> 01:03:58,810
But how did you find out about this, Inspector Shiratori?

1018
01:03:58,910 --> 01:04:01,110
Did you learn about it from Inspector Ayanakoji?

1019
01:04:01,310 --> 01:04:02,510
No.

1020
01:04:02,610 --> 01:04:04,110
Don't underestimate me.

1021
01:04:04,210 --> 01:04:06,410
I've got my ways in Gion.

1022
01:04:07,110 --> 01:04:08,410
Is that something to be proud of?

1023
01:04:08,710 --> 01:04:12,410
Although that guy is my opponent,

1024
01:04:12,510 --> 01:04:15,410
I don't want to be compared with someone
who always carries a chipmunk.

1025
01:04:15,410 --> 01:04:16,710
Chipmunk?

1026
01:04:17,010 --> 01:04:18,910
He always has it in his pocket.

1027
01:04:19,110 --> 01:04:22,310
At least he didn't bring it to the scene of the crime.

1028
01:04:22,410 --> 01:04:23,610
Chipmunk?

1029
01:04:25,010 --> 01:04:27,210
This is Inspector Shiratori.

1030
01:04:27,210 --> 01:04:28,510
This is Megure.

1031
01:04:28,610 --> 01:04:32,410
Another possibility emerged in the Benkei and Yoshitsune case.

1032
01:04:32,810 --> 01:04:34,310
Belongings.

1033
01:04:34,510 --> 01:04:36,810
If you think about it this way, the riddle will be solved.

1034
01:04:36,910 --> 01:04:43,210
In other words, we reasoned that Benkei or Yoshitsune
might be dead already.

1035
01:04:44,610 --> 01:04:46,210
I see!

1036
01:04:56,610 --> 01:04:57,710
Mr. Mouri.

1037
01:04:57,710 --> 01:05:01,610
Do you really know who murdered Mr. Sakura?

1038
01:05:01,710 --> 01:05:02,610
Yes

1039
01:05:04,410 --> 01:05:06,310
Now, please listen.

1040
01:05:06,510 --> 01:05:10,510
The murderer is you, Ms. Suzu Chika.

1041
01:05:11,010 --> 01:05:12,110
Nonsense!

1042
01:05:13,210 --> 01:05:15,010
What a mess!

1043
01:05:15,210 --> 01:05:16,610
Is he okay?

1044
01:05:16,610 --> 01:05:18,710
Anyway, let him finish first.

1045
01:05:20,310 --> 01:05:23,410
The motive is to avenge your father who got killed.

1046
01:05:23,410 --> 01:05:28,310
Your father is Yoshitsune, the leader of the gang of robbers.

1047
01:05:29,510 --> 01:05:34,110
Yoshitsune was killed by his men who betrayed him three months ago,

1048
01:05:34,310 --> 01:05:37,010
so the money that got sent to Suzu Chika also stopped.

1049
01:05:37,210 --> 01:05:38,210
I see.

1050
01:05:38,910 --> 01:05:41,410
You have another accomplice,

1051
01:05:41,710 --> 01:05:42,810
Benkei.

1052
01:05:42,810 --> 01:05:44,310
Benkei?

1053
01:05:44,610 --> 01:05:46,510
Who is this Benkei?

1054
01:05:46,810 --> 01:05:48,510
Inspector Ayanokoji.

1055
01:05:48,510 --> 01:05:49,310
It's you.

1056
01:05:51,610 --> 01:05:54,710
Ms. Suzu Chika, when you went to the teahouse,

1057
01:05:54,710 --> 01:05:56,910
you had something with you.

1058
01:05:57,010 --> 01:06:01,410
The dagger and the chipmunk raised by Inspector Ayanakoji.

1059
01:06:04,310 --> 01:06:05,310
So cute!

1060
01:06:05,710 --> 01:06:08,810
This chipmunk is the key to the crime.

1061
01:06:08,910 --> 01:06:14,010
Ms. Suzu Chika, you pretended to go to the bathroom
in the middle of the banquet,

1062
01:06:14,010 --> 01:06:16,010
and went on to kill Mr. Sakura in the warehouse.

1063
01:06:16,110 --> 01:06:19,110
You tied the short knife on the chipmunk that hid there in advance,

1064
01:06:19,210 --> 01:06:23,010
and then let it out from the glass window.

1065
01:06:23,510 --> 01:06:27,510
The chipmunk jumped into the river
and swam to the lower reaches of the river,

1066
01:06:28,310 --> 01:06:31,610
where Inspector Ayanokoji awaited to retrieve the knife.

1067
01:06:31,610 --> 01:06:35,010
He then used this knife to attack Heiji.

1068
01:06:35,310 --> 01:06:36,210
I see!

1069
01:06:36,210 --> 01:06:39,710
So that splashing sound was caused
by the chipmunk jumping into the water.

1070
01:06:40,010 --> 01:06:43,710
Other than the case of Mr. Sakura, the other two crimes
were also committed by the two of you.

1071
01:06:44,010 --> 01:06:46,510
Inspector, do you know archery?

1072
01:06:46,610 --> 01:06:49,810
For something so troublesome, how would I know it?

1073
01:06:50,210 --> 01:06:51,310
Is that so?

1074
01:06:52,810 --> 01:06:54,510
But Ms. Suzu Chika,

1075
01:06:54,810 --> 01:06:56,010
I heard that people who practice archery

1076
01:06:56,010 --> 01:06:59,610
often get themselves injured at this very spot.

1077
01:06:59,810 --> 01:07:01,210
It's true.

1078
01:07:01,510 --> 01:07:05,310
This wound of mine indeed came from archery practice,

1079
01:07:07,610 --> 01:07:09,310
but I just started learning it.

1080
01:07:09,310 --> 01:07:12,210
How could I possibly kill someone with it?

1081
01:07:12,510 --> 01:07:14,410
That's what I thought, too.

1082
01:07:14,510 --> 01:07:17,610
This should be proof that she's a beginner
because she has a wound near her thumb.

1083
01:07:17,610 --> 01:07:20,510
I heard this from my friends in the archery club.

1084
01:07:20,710 --> 01:07:24,310
And the deceased had no reason to divide the belongings.

1085
01:07:24,310 --> 01:07:25,810
Mr. Mouri,

1086
01:07:25,810 --> 01:07:29,010
do you really think that this girl is a murderer?

1087
01:07:29,010 --> 01:07:30,010
Well...

1088
01:07:30,010 --> 01:07:31,610
Stop joking.

1089
01:07:31,710 --> 01:07:35,010
This kid is very busy with singing, dancing and tea ceremony,

1090
01:07:35,010 --> 01:07:37,710
where does she get the time to kill?

1091
01:07:39,310 --> 01:07:40,010
What?

1092
01:07:40,010 --> 01:07:41,310
That chipmunk,

1093
01:07:41,310 --> 01:07:44,610
I'm afraid it can't carry a short knife with such a small body.

1094
01:07:45,110 --> 01:07:46,310
So annoying.

1095
01:07:46,510 --> 01:07:48,510
I'll prove it to you.

1096
01:07:51,210 --> 01:07:53,410
Move, chipmunk.

1097
01:07:53,910 --> 01:07:56,010
I can't stand it anymore.

1098
01:07:56,310 --> 01:08:00,210
You are acting like this to get out of the crime, aren't you?

1099
01:08:01,810 --> 01:08:03,310
Stop it.

1100
01:08:03,310 --> 01:08:06,010
Poor chipmunk, uncle.

1101
01:08:06,210 --> 01:08:08,010
This is animal cruelty.

1102
01:08:08,210 --> 01:08:10,210
Shut up, you kids.

1103
01:08:10,310 --> 01:08:12,310
Genta, save the chipmunk.

1104
01:08:12,310 --> 01:08:13,110
Okay.

1105
01:08:13,710 --> 01:08:14,610
Kudo.

1106
01:08:16,810 --> 01:08:19,710
Thanks to Uncle, I got the murderer now.

1107
01:08:20,110 --> 01:08:21,410
Me, too.

1108
01:08:21,510 --> 01:08:25,110
It had to be someone good at archery to say such a thing.

1109
01:08:25,410 --> 01:08:27,210
We just need evidence now.

1110
01:08:28,310 --> 01:08:30,310
And the whereabouts of that Buddha statue.

1111
01:08:30,610 --> 01:08:33,010
Little chipmunk, poor baby.

1112
01:08:33,110 --> 01:08:35,310
Let's feed it with something.

1113
01:08:35,510 --> 01:08:37,210
I have an acorn.

1114
01:08:42,910 --> 01:08:45,510
This feels like the children's song, "Donguri Koro Koro".

1115
01:08:45,710 --> 01:08:47,410
Donguri Koro Koro.

1116
01:08:48,410 --> 01:08:49,510
Could it be...

1117
01:08:54,510 --> 01:08:56,110
What's wrong, Kudo?

1118
01:08:56,210 --> 01:09:01,210
It suddenly occurred to me that the copy
of the painting might refer to the name of a street in Kyoto.

1119
01:09:01,310 --> 01:09:02,310
What are you saying?

1120
01:09:06,110 --> 01:09:08,010
The first is the east-west street.

1121
01:09:08,340 --> 01:09:10,020
If the fifth floor is

1122
01:09:10,260 --> 01:09:12,040
(Fifth Street)
the fifth street

1123
01:09:12,540 --> 01:09:13,540
and the fourth floor

1124
01:09:14,140 --> 01:09:15,310
(Fourth Street)
is the fourth street.

1125
01:09:15,910 --> 01:09:18,220
Between the third floor and the second floor,

1126
01:09:18,320 --> 01:09:20,150
that's the middle of the third and second street.

1127
01:09:20,460 --> 01:09:22,120
(Oike Street)
That's Oike Street.

1128
01:09:22,310 --> 01:09:23,700
(Oike Street)
Then the evidence for this is would be...

1129
01:09:24,910 --> 01:09:26,510
Donguri Koro Koro.

1130
01:09:27,410 --> 01:09:29,410
Then there is a north-south road.

1131
01:09:29,840 --> 01:09:32,610
(Ogawa Street)
There is a song called "Ogawa Spring" that talks about violets.

1132
01:09:32,700 --> 01:09:33,810
(Ogawa Street)
So it's Ogawa Street.

1133
01:09:34,280 --> 01:09:36,100
(Karasuma Street)
Tengu is mentioned in "Karasu Tengu".

1134
01:09:36,210 --> 01:09:37,410
(Karasuma Street)
So it's Karasuma Street.

1135
01:09:37,810 --> 01:09:39,800
(Mount Fuji)
Then there is the character of Mt. Fuji,

1136
01:09:39,900 --> 01:09:42,520
(Tominokoji Street)
so it is Tominokoji Street.

1137
01:09:43,010 --> 01:09:44,910
What is that chicken?

1138
01:09:45,110 --> 01:09:47,010
The loach is probably the "Yanagi Pot".

1139
01:09:47,110 --> 01:09:49,560
(Yanaginobanba Street)
So it's Yanaginobanba Street?

1140
01:09:49,710 --> 01:09:51,010
Chicken is...

1141
01:09:51,810 --> 01:09:54,410
Isn't it Nishinotoin Street?

1142
01:09:54,750 --> 01:09:57,410
(Nishinotoin Street)
Because the chicken head points to the west.

1143
01:09:57,810 --> 01:09:59,610
That's so hard.

1144
01:10:00,510 --> 01:10:02,910
And what's this?

1145
01:10:05,210 --> 01:10:07,310
The cicada is of the "large brown cicada",

1146
01:10:07,310 --> 01:10:08,920
(Aburanokoji Street)
so it is Aburanokoji Street.

1147
01:10:09,100 --> 01:10:10,800
(Youkoji Street)
Tengu is Toromaru Street.

1148
01:10:11,380 --> 01:10:12,600
Goldfish eats wheat bran,

1149
01:10:12,760 --> 01:10:16,240
(Fuyacho Street)
so it's Fuyacho Street.

1150
01:10:16,310 --> 01:10:19,610
Then the violets and Mount Fuji share the same color.

1151
01:10:19,610 --> 01:10:22,110
Chicken and loach, cicada and goldfish

1152
01:10:22,110 --> 01:10:24,710
Then connect Tengu with Tengu.

1153
01:10:24,710 --> 01:10:27,710
King? What's with this word "King"?

1154
01:10:30,310 --> 01:10:31,110
There's an extra dot.

1155
01:10:31,710 --> 01:10:32,710
It should be like this.

1156
01:10:36,010 --> 01:10:39,310
Jade, meaning there's a treasure.

1157
01:10:40,010 --> 01:10:41,010
So this place is...

1158
01:10:42,310 --> 01:10:43,610
Bukkoji Temple.

1159
01:10:44,310 --> 01:10:46,810
This is where we find the treasure.

1160
01:11:05,510 --> 01:11:06,510
What's wrong?

1161
01:11:07,010 --> 01:11:09,870
I'm feeling a bit dizzy.

1162
01:11:09,910 --> 01:11:12,210
(Rokkaku Temple)

1163
01:11:15,110 --> 01:11:16,210
Excuse me.

1164
01:11:16,410 --> 01:11:18,510
How do you feel?

1165
01:11:19,810 --> 01:11:21,410
Much better.

1166
01:11:22,110 --> 01:11:23,010
Hattori.

1167
01:11:23,510 --> 01:11:27,610
You sneaked into Sannou Temple eight years ago, didn't you?

1168
01:11:27,910 --> 01:11:29,610
How did you know that?

1169
01:11:29,610 --> 01:11:30,610
Idiot.

1170
01:11:30,610 --> 01:11:34,110
I knew everything when I saw your expression
when you were looking at the cherry blossoms.

1171
01:11:34,210 --> 01:11:37,310
There happened to be the lattice window you mentioned.

1172
01:11:39,110 --> 01:11:39,910
Yeah.

1173
01:11:40,410 --> 01:11:44,210
I found this crystal bead just under the cherry blossom tree.

1174
01:11:44,510 --> 01:11:46,310
I don't want to disappoint you.

1175
01:11:46,510 --> 01:11:47,610
But this crystal bead,

1176
01:11:47,810 --> 01:11:51,510
I'm afraid it wasn't from your first crush.

1177
01:11:51,810 --> 01:11:53,110
What are you saying?

1178
01:11:53,540 --> 01:11:54,820
I'm afraid this is

1179
01:11:54,940 --> 01:11:59,500
(Urna)
the urna on the forehead of the stolen Buddha statue in Sannou Temple.

1180
01:11:59,640 --> 01:12:00,910
Urna.

1181
01:12:00,910 --> 01:12:05,210
Is it the shiny thing in the middle of the Buddha's forehead?

1182
01:12:05,210 --> 01:12:05,810
Yep.

1183
01:12:06,510 --> 01:12:09,910
Buddha statues often use crystal beads to make urna.

1184
01:12:10,210 --> 01:12:12,110
The masks in Noh plays are also like this.

1185
01:12:13,110 --> 01:12:15,110
This is what I think.

1186
01:12:15,210 --> 01:12:18,110
Eight years ago, the Genjibotaru gang

1187
01:12:18,610 --> 01:12:20,710
sneaked into the Sannou Temple,

1188
01:12:20,910 --> 01:12:23,110
and stole the hidden Buddha statue.

1189
01:12:26,510 --> 01:12:28,710
But on the way out,

1190
01:12:28,710 --> 01:12:30,810
the urna fell off.

1191
01:12:37,510 --> 01:12:40,310
The leader, Yoshitsune, noticed this

1192
01:12:40,310 --> 01:12:43,110
and sent a subordinate to find it at Sannou Temple.

1193
01:12:43,110 --> 01:12:44,210
Right then...

1194
01:12:57,310 --> 01:12:58,610
I want red bean soup.

1195
01:12:58,710 --> 01:13:00,510
I want honey bean ice.

1196
01:13:02,810 --> 01:13:07,510
The helpless leader kept the Buddha statue
in the warehouse that Mr. Sakura searched in.

1197
01:13:07,510 --> 01:13:10,510
But eight years later, the murderer found out by accident

1198
01:13:10,610 --> 01:13:14,210
that you were the boy from eight years ago.

1199
01:13:14,410 --> 01:13:15,810
Because of the magazine?

1200
01:13:19,110 --> 01:13:20,110
At the same time,

1201
01:13:20,210 --> 01:13:22,710
there were also incidents inside the gang.

1202
01:13:22,810 --> 01:13:26,110
I think the leader might have been seriously ill.

1203
01:13:26,410 --> 01:13:28,110
The leader knows that he's dying,

1204
01:13:28,210 --> 01:13:32,110
so he hid the Buddha statue he stole from Sannou Temple elsewhere.

1205
01:13:32,310 --> 01:13:36,110
He then divided the hits of the location to his men in pieces.

1206
01:13:36,810 --> 01:13:41,110
He left his last words, stating that the one
who solves the riddle will become the new leader.

1207
01:13:42,710 --> 01:13:45,110
He then died.

1208
01:13:45,210 --> 01:13:50,410
The men desperately tried to solve the riddle, but failed.

1209
01:13:50,510 --> 01:13:51,310
At that time,

1210
01:13:51,710 --> 01:13:54,210
Mr. Sakura

1211
01:13:54,310 --> 01:13:56,510
actively reached out to the murderer for collaboration.

1212
01:13:56,910 --> 01:14:03,210
He used the murderer's swordsmanship
to kill all the other accomplices,

1213
01:14:03,310 --> 01:14:07,910
then the two of them would go look for the Buddha statue and urna,

1214
01:14:07,910 --> 01:14:11,110
and then split money from selling it.

1215
01:14:11,210 --> 01:14:12,110
Yes.

1216
01:14:12,410 --> 01:14:17,210
I'm afraid only Mr. Sakura, the only antique dealer in the gang,

1217
01:14:17,310 --> 01:14:20,510
had the channels for selling the stolen goods.

1218
01:14:20,610 --> 01:14:23,910
That's why he firmly believed that he was absolutely safe.

1219
01:14:24,210 --> 01:14:27,310
The murderer pretended to listen to Mr. Sakura.

1220
01:14:27,410 --> 01:14:29,610
But he actually had planned to

1221
01:14:29,610 --> 01:14:32,110
kill all the accomplices and to take the treasure for himself.

1222
01:14:32,310 --> 01:14:33,810
But to achieve this,

1223
01:14:34,000 --> 01:14:37,400
(Bukkoji Temple)in any case, he had to solve
the riddle of the painting left by the leader.

1224
01:14:38,010 --> 01:14:39,310
So the murderer...

1225
01:14:39,410 --> 01:14:43,610
Thought of having the famous detective,
Kogoro Mouri, to solve the riddle for him.

1226
01:14:45,010 --> 01:14:47,410
Bukkoji Temple, we're here.

1227
01:14:49,510 --> 01:14:53,310
But is the Buddha statue really hidden here?

1228
01:14:53,610 --> 01:14:55,810
I have a feeling that something's wrong.

1229
01:14:59,810 --> 01:15:00,810
What is it?

1230
01:15:01,010 --> 01:15:03,310
Kudo, what have you got?

1231
01:15:04,910 --> 01:15:05,910
This…

1232
01:15:09,910 --> 01:15:11,210
Gyokuryuji Temple

1233
01:15:11,410 --> 01:15:13,910
The point in the painting, could it refer to this?

1234
01:15:16,110 --> 01:15:17,710
Toyama. It's me.

1235
01:15:17,810 --> 01:15:19,710
The girl's with me.

1236
01:15:20,010 --> 01:15:24,010
Come to the Gyokuryuji Temple on Mount Kurama alone an hour later.

1237
01:15:24,110 --> 01:15:25,910
If you dare call the police,

1238
01:15:25,910 --> 01:15:27,410
she'll be dead.

1239
01:15:27,510 --> 01:15:30,210
Heiji, don't come. You'll get yourself killed!

1240
01:15:30,310 --> 01:15:31,910
Toyama, Toyama!

1241
01:15:32,810 --> 01:15:33,610
Hattori.

1242
01:15:33,610 --> 01:15:37,010
It's Toyama. She got kidnapped.

1243
01:15:37,110 --> 01:15:37,610
What?

1244
01:15:37,710 --> 01:15:38,810
He asked me to get to Gyokuryuji Temple on Mount Kurama

1245
01:15:38,810 --> 01:15:41,910
an hour later by myself.

1246
01:15:42,010 --> 01:15:43,210
Gyokuryuji Temple.

1247
01:15:46,410 --> 01:15:48,210
Good.

1248
01:15:48,810 --> 01:15:50,910
Let's go together now.

1249
01:15:55,310 --> 01:15:56,310
Hattori!

1250
01:15:57,090 --> 01:16:00,180
(Modoribashi Bridge)

1251
01:16:00,350 --> 01:16:04,370
The dutiful son who learned of his father's death
hurried back to Kyoto.

1252
01:16:04,370 --> 01:16:07,710
It just so happened that the funeral procession passed this bridge.

1253
01:16:07,710 --> 01:16:11,390
At that moment, the father suddenly woke.

1254
01:16:11,390 --> 01:16:14,870
Legend has it, the father and the dutiful son got to speak in the end.

1255
01:16:17,610 --> 01:16:18,710
Hello.

1256
01:16:20,910 --> 01:16:23,490
(Mount Kurama)

1257
01:16:23,750 --> 01:16:26,540
(Gyokuryuji Temple)

1258
01:16:38,010 --> 01:16:39,510
The leader has instructed

1259
01:16:39,610 --> 01:16:41,010
that the knife will be placed in Benkei's drawer.

1260
01:16:41,010 --> 01:16:43,310
The bows and arrows are in the Rokkaku drawer.

1261
01:16:43,810 --> 01:16:46,810
Benkei's drawer is in...

1262
01:16:47,610 --> 01:16:49,810
Starting from the top, 1 2 3...

1263
01:16:50,410 --> 01:16:51,510
What are you talking about?

1264
01:16:51,610 --> 01:16:53,810
Benkei and Rokkaku drawer.

1265
01:16:54,410 --> 01:16:55,810
Bukkoji Temple?

1266
01:16:56,110 --> 01:16:58,910
I heard the two of them saying that.

1267
01:17:04,910 --> 01:17:07,810
Seriously, where did those two go?

1268
01:17:08,010 --> 01:17:11,010
Toyama didn't answer her phone either.

1269
01:17:11,710 --> 01:17:13,210
Bukkoji Temple.

1270
01:17:13,410 --> 01:17:14,310
I'm hungry.

1271
01:17:14,510 --> 01:17:16,410
Really? We'll be home soon.

1272
01:17:16,510 --> 01:17:17,510
Excuse me,

1273
01:17:18,110 --> 01:17:21,310
where is this Gyokuryuji Temple?

1274
01:17:21,410 --> 01:17:23,410
In the deep mountains of Mount Kurama.

1275
01:17:23,510 --> 01:17:27,210
But I heard that it was abandoned a long time ago.

1276
01:17:27,510 --> 01:17:28,710
Thanks.

1277
01:17:30,710 --> 01:17:32,210
Kurama Mountain.

1278
01:17:41,210 --> 01:17:42,310
So slow.

1279
01:17:42,910 --> 01:17:46,210
Knowing that it is a trap, how can one be fooled so easily?

1280
01:17:46,410 --> 01:17:48,010
Really?

1281
01:17:48,110 --> 01:17:50,810
Probably just scared.

1282
01:17:55,310 --> 01:17:56,410
Heiji.

1283
01:18:10,410 --> 01:18:11,610
You didn't hurt Toyama,

1284
01:18:11,810 --> 01:18:13,910
did you?

1285
01:18:14,610 --> 01:18:17,010
I'm fine, Heiji.

1286
01:18:17,510 --> 01:18:20,710
This is what you really wanted, right?

1287
01:18:24,510 --> 01:18:27,310
In order to retrieve this crystal bead,

1288
01:18:27,410 --> 01:18:30,110
you attacked me here yesterday.

1289
01:18:30,210 --> 01:18:32,010
But you failed.

1290
01:18:32,310 --> 01:18:35,410
Then, to take this treasure for your own,

1291
01:18:35,410 --> 01:18:38,610
you killed Mr. Sakura at the teahouse in Ponto-cho.

1292
01:18:39,010 --> 01:18:43,010
Why did you choose Ponto-cho instead of other places?

1293
01:18:43,110 --> 01:18:46,510
Because it was the only place with a river
flowing behind the teahouse.

1294
01:18:46,610 --> 01:18:47,610
River?

1295
01:18:47,710 --> 01:18:51,510
After you killed Mr. Sakura who was looking for
the Buddha statue in the warehouse,

1296
01:18:51,910 --> 01:18:55,510
you placed the company's anti-theft tracker
used to find missing children

1297
01:18:55,510 --> 01:18:58,710
in an empty bottle with the weapon, and dumped them together.

1298
01:19:00,710 --> 01:19:05,710
Then you logged into the security company's webpage
with your mobile phone,

1299
01:19:05,810 --> 01:19:08,610
