1300
01:19:08,910 --> 01:19:12,510
You then hid and waited for me,

1301
01:19:12,610 --> 01:19:15,110
trying to kill me with the same short knife.

1302
01:19:18,110 --> 01:19:21,510
Although you failed because of Tomoya,

1303
01:19:21,610 --> 01:19:25,110
you deliberately left a short knife for disguise,

1304
01:19:25,210 --> 01:19:29,110
so that people would think it was the murderer
who fled the tea house with a weapon.

1305
01:19:29,310 --> 01:19:31,810
Right, Mr. Saijo?

1306
01:19:31,910 --> 01:19:35,410
No, maybe I should call you Musashibo Benkei.

1307
01:19:41,210 --> 01:19:45,610
Indeed the high school detective, Heiji Hattori, from Naniwa Castle.

1308
01:19:45,710 --> 01:19:47,810
How did you know that I am the murderer?

1309
01:19:47,910 --> 01:19:51,710
Because you pretended that you didn't know archery.

1310
01:19:51,810 --> 01:19:53,710
But when you sat,

1311
01:19:53,810 --> 01:19:56,410
you moved your right foot back half a step before sitting down.

1312
01:19:56,470 --> 01:19:58,410
(Half-foot drag)
That is called "half-foot drag".

1313
01:19:58,410 --> 01:20:01,940
(Half-foot drag)
People who practice archery have the habit of sitting like that.

1314
01:20:02,260 --> 01:20:06,230
(The pronunciation of arrow pillow is the same as Yamakura)
So when asked who knows archery,

1315
01:20:06,610 --> 01:20:08,540
