01:36:50,410 --> 01:36:51,410
What?

1559
01:36:52,410 --> 01:36:53,210
Nothing.

1560
01:36:54,610 --> 01:36:57,110
Sure enough, it was just a dream.

1561
01:37:20,520 --> 01:37:22,110
(Sannou Temple  Morning)

1562
01:37:22,510 --> 01:37:24,010
I'm so sorry.

1563
01:37:24,110 --> 01:37:26,810
In the end, I couldn't find the Buddha statue for you.

1564
01:37:27,010 --> 01:37:27,810
It's okay.

1565
01:37:27,910 --> 01:37:31,310
Don't mention it. It's the Buddha's decision.

1566
01:37:31,610 --> 01:37:33,710
Don't worry about it.

1567
01:37:33,910 --> 01:37:36,410
Everyone, take care.

1568
01:37:38,510 --> 01:37:39,710
Goodbye.

1569
01:37:46,710 --> 01:37:49,210
But it's really difficult now.

1570
01:37:49,410 --> 01:37:52,910
We only got one hour before the consecration ceremony.

1571
01:37:53,110 --> 01:37:54,310
What's so rough?

1572
01:37:54,510 --> 01:37:57,210
If you have it, you can show it. If not, then leave it.

1573
01:38:05,510 --> 01:38:09,710
Bhaisajyaguru is back.

1574
01:38:11,920 --> 01:38:14,050
(Gyokuryuji Temple  Early morning)

1575
01:38:20,610 --> 01:38:22,110
I found it, Kudo.

1576
01:38:22,310 --> 01:38:24,110
Like I said.

1577
01:38:28,410 --> 01:38:31,410
Unexpectedly, the shape of the temple was arranged in the word "Jade".

1578
01:38:31,510 --> 01:38:34,010
And the dot sits right at the clock tower.

1579
01:38:35,310 --> 01:38:38,210
I didn't even notice it.

1580
01:38:38,310 --> 01:38:41,910
Add a cover to "Jade", it becomes “Treasure”.

1581
01:38:42,310 --> 01:38:45,110
And treasure cover refers to the roof.

1582
01:38:45,210 --> 01:38:46,610
I see.

1583
01:38:54,910 --> 01:38:56,810
It's as good as ever.

1584
01:38:56,910 --> 01:38:57,810
Yes.

1585
01:39:01,510 --> 01:39:04,410
Those two guys are really the best of partners.

1586
01:39:04,810 --> 01:39:07,710
Just like Yoshitsune and Benkei.

1587
01:39:08,710 --> 01:39:12,710
Detective Hattori and Mouri?

1588
01:39:12,910 --> 01:39:16,110
It seems that you still need practice.

1589
01:39:21,010 --> 01:39:22,210
What?

1590
01:39:25,710 --> 01:39:28,710
So next up, Ayumi.

1591
01:39:28,810 --> 01:39:29,710
Okay.

1592
01:39:30,010 --> 01:39:32,010
It's so cute.

1593
01:39:32,110 --> 01:39:34,010
I really want to take you home.

1594
01:39:34,110 --> 01:39:37,410
Not this. It's my best friend.

1595
01:39:37,710 --> 01:39:41,610
Inspector, you don't have a lot of human friends?

1596
01:39:43,310 --> 01:39:47,010
I mistook you two as murderers, so sorry.

1597
01:39:47,110 --> 01:39:48,310
No problem.

1598
01:39:48,510 --> 01:39:51,810
Actually, I knew who my father was。

1599
01:39:51,910 --> 01:39:55,610
And I told him that he didn't have to send me money anymore.

1600
01:39:56,410 --> 01:39:57,810
Who is

1601
01:39:57,910 --> 01:39:58,910
your father?

1602
01:39:59,210 --> 01:40:00,710
That's a secret.

1603
01:40:05,410 --> 01:40:09,010
That old bald donkey.

1604
01:40:11,210 --> 01:40:15,410
Maru-Take-Ebisu-Ni-Oshi-Oike

1605
01:40:15,710 --> 01:40:17,310
Yome-san-Rokkaku-Tako-Nishiki…

1606
01:40:17,310 --> 01:40:20,110
Not a "yome" but an "ane", fool.

1607
01:40:20,510 --> 01:40:22,610
Where did you learn this song?

1608
01:40:22,810 --> 01:40:25,010
From relatives in Kyoto,

1609
01:40:25,110 --> 01:40:28,110
when I was in the third grade of elementary school.

1610
01:40:28,210 --> 01:40:31,410
I learned it when I went with you.

1611
01:40:31,510 --> 01:40:32,510
With me?

1612
01:40:32,510 --> 01:40:34,410
You don't remember?

1613
01:40:34,710 --> 01:40:38,310
I wasn't even ready but you couldn't wait,

1614
01:40:38,410 --> 01:40:41,910
and said you wanted to go and play at Sannou Temple. So you ran out.

1615
01:40:42,010 --> 01:40:45,510
My relatives dressed me in a kimono,

1616
01:40:45,610 --> 01:40:49,010
and I put my hair in a bun with some makeup.

1617
01:40:49,510 --> 01:40:52,310
Then I went to Sannou Temple to look for you.

1618
01:40:52,410 --> 01:40:53,510
But I couldn't find you.

1619
01:40:53,510 --> 01:40:55,610
So I played with the ball for a while and went back.

1620
01:40:56,310 --> 01:40:57,110
Seriously though,

1621
01:40:57,110 --> 01:40:59,310
I wanted to let you see

1622
01:40:59,410 --> 01:41:02,910
that cherry blossom tree. It was so beautiful
with the cherry blossoms falling down.

1623
01:41:03,510 --> 01:41:08,510
Maru-Take-Ebisu-Ni-Oshi-Oike

1624
01:41:08,810 --> 01:41:13,510
Yome-san-Rokkaku-Tako-Nishiki…

1625
01:41:18,410 --> 01:41:20,810
Finally,

1626
01:41:21,810 --> 01:41:22,710
we meet again.

1627
01:41:22,810 --> 01:41:25,110
Did you see your first love? Heiji.

1628
01:41:25,210 --> 01:41:27,310
Who is it? That geisha?

1629
01:41:27,710 --> 01:41:30,510
I won't tell you, ever, idiot.

1630
01:41:30,610 --> 01:41:32,710
You petty kid, tell me!

1631
01:41:32,810 --> 01:41:36,710
Or maybe I will tell you in 1500 years.

1632
01:41:37,210 --> 01:41:38,510
What?

1633
01:41:50,910 --> 01:41:53,610
Conan, what are you doing?

1634
01:41:58,210 --> 01:42:00,210
Why are you sweating so much?

1635
01:42:00,910 --> 01:42:03,510
Shinichi.

1636
01:42:04,510 --> 01:42:08,010
Speaking of that, I called Shinichi

1637
01:42:08,110 --> 01:42:11,810
and asked him to act as Heiji to save Toyama,

1638
01:42:12,210 --> 01:42:12,710
right?

1639
01:42:13,610 --> 01:42:17,510
Yeah, but that guy is really weak.

1640
01:42:17,710 --> 01:42:20,110
He ran away midway.

1641
01:42:20,210 --> 01:42:23,310
Told me not to tell and he said it first.

1642
01:42:26,610 --> 01:42:27,910
That's right.

1643
01:42:28,110 --> 01:42:31,910
So it was Shinichi after all.

1644
01:42:34,810 --> 01:42:36,710
I finally saw you.

1645
01:46:55,510 --> 01:46:57,010
I want an ice cream.

1646
01:46:57,110 --> 01:46:57,610
OK.

1647
01:46:57,810 --> 01:46:59,210
300 yen.

1648
01:47:00,710 --> 01:47:04,610
I'm the only one who didn't see the person
I wanted to meet in the end.

1649
01:47:04,910 --> 01:47:07,410
Suzuki will definitely see Kyogoku-kun soon.

1650
01:47:07,410 --> 01:47:08,510
Most definitely.

1651
01:47:08,710 --> 01:47:14,010
But I have no patience to wait for people.

1652
01:47:14,510 --> 01:47:16,110
Isn't Ran the same?

1653
01:47:17,010 --> 01:47:20,010
I don't hate waiting for someone.

1654
01:47:20,910 --> 01:47:24,010
Because the longer you wait,

1655
01:47:24,010 --> 01:47:25,310
when we meet again...

1656
01:47:28,710 --> 01:47:31,710
Your expression is still the same as then.

1657
01:47:32,210 --> 01:47:33,810
the happier we will be.

1658
01:47:34,810 --> 01:47:36,910
Darn,

1659
01:47:36,910 --> 01:47:39,410
I really want Kudo to hear this cheesy line.

